The evidence with the title 'Pat Toomey - Wikipedia ' says In 2013, Toomey was one of 18 Senators who voted against the bill to reopen the government during the United States government shutdown of 2013. Regarding the vote, he said: "the one major redeeming aspect of this bill is that it reopens the government  ... But i can not support piling hundreds of billions of dollars of debt  ... 
